/>
<?php if($this->CompileMode==''):?>
<small><i>Mode is empty string - you are in development environment.</i></small>
<?php elseif($this->CompileMode=='SFU'):?>
<small><i>Single File Mode - to generate all assets in <code><b>/Var/Tmp</b></code> directory.</i></small>
<?php elseif(strpos($this->CompileMode,'PHP')===0):?>
<small><i>Application is packed as single PHP file.</i></small>
<?php elseif(strpos($this->CompileMode,'PHAR')===0):?>
<small><i>Application is packed as standard PHAR archive.</i></small>
<?php endif;?></p><hr
/><h2>Follow these steps how to create and build single file app:</h2><h3>
<a
class="clickable-link" href="javascript:void(0);">
Wrap <code>Hello World</code> example with a portable structure
</a></h3><div
class="clickable-content hidden">
<small>Open command line in localhost directory and run:</small>
<code
class="shell"><div
class="comment"># load new hello world portable project structure</div><div
class="command">composer create-project mvccore/example-helloworld-portable</div><div
class="comment"># go to portable project directory</div><div
class="command">cd example-helloworld-portable</div><div
class="comment"># load the same hello world project into new ./development dir<br
/>
# (or simply just copy this same project into the new ./development dir)</div><div
class="command">composer create-project mvccore/example-helloworld ./development</div><div
class="comment"># go to hello world project directory</div><div
class="command">cd ./development</div><div
class="comment"># update dependencies for hello world development sources</div><div
class="command">composer update</div>
</code></div><h3>
<a
class="clickable-link" href="javascript:void(0);">
Prepare and run build process
</a></h3><div
class="clickable-content hidden"><ol><li>Go to <code>example-helloworld-portable/development</code> directory</li><li>Clear everything in <code>/Var/Tmp</code> directory.</li><li>
Add <code>TRUE</code> param into <code>index.php</code>: <br
/>
<code>\MvcCore\Application::GetInstance()->Run();</code><br
/>
to&nbsp;temporary switch application compile <br
/>mode to&nbsp; <b>SFU</b> (<b>S</b>ingle <b>F</b>ile <b>U</b>rl mode).</li><li>
Visit all application routes where are different CSS or&nbsp;JS assets groups
to&nbsp;complete all possible asset files in&nbsp; <code>/Var/Tmp</code>
directory. Process those requests on&nbsp;addresses with the same or&nbsp;empty
request base path as&nbsp;result application will have.</li><li>Go to <code>example-helloworld-portable/build</code> directory</li><li>
Run <b><code>./make-php.php</code></b> script in&nbsp;browser
or&nbsp;in&nbsp;CLI to&nbsp;build result application. Do not
include any PHP autoloaders, any unnecessary code you don't
need and do not include any source CSS/JS files which are
not necessary.</li><li>
Visit your application in browser somewhere on <br
/>
<b><code>http://localhost/example-helloworld-portable/release/</code></b><br
/>
and enjoy result.</li></ol></div>
